  "articleSummary": "The article **analyzes NVMe SSD performance and pricing across cloud providers**, emphasizing AWS EC2's i3.xlarge instances as the most cost-effective and high-performing option for I/O-intensive workloads. It highlights AWS's i3.xlarge/i3.2xlarge instances with NVMe SSDs (up to 1.9TB) as offering competitive price/performance ratios (e.g., $110–$450/month) and speeds exceeding 1GB/s, though real-world network throughput often falls short of advertised rates. The analysis targets cloud engineers and DevOps professionals seeking optimized storage solutions, using benchmark data and cost comparisons to frame AWS as the leader in this niche. The tone is technical and data-driven, with a focus on practical trade-offs between cost, speed, and scalability. Key framing includes \"Price vs. I/O Performance\" and \"Head to Head\" comparisons to underscore AWS's dominance in this segment.",
